name: N-boc-3-(2-thienyl)-L-alanine

The thienyl group introduces a rigid structure with potential hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by approximately +30°C. The methylene bridge introduces additional rigidity, contributing approximately +5°C. The carbonyl group introduces polar carbonyl interactions, raising the melting point by approximately +40°C. The presence of a methoxy group can also contribute to an increase in molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, with an approximate increase of +5°C.
